; hyperoperators, similar to Perl 6

; !>< spreads a function between to lists
!>< ^+ [1 2 3] [4 5 6]

; !<< upgrades the left argument to an array with the length of the right argument
!<< ^+ 1 [1 2 3]

; !>> upgrades the right argument
!>> ^+ [1 2 3] 1

; !<> upgrades any argument to the array with the biggest length
!<> ^+ 1 [1 2 3]
!<> ^+ [1 2 3] 1
!<> ^+ [1 2] [1 2 3 4 5]
